REFERENCE DETAILS

Exact implementation pattern (imperative loop):
- for i from 1 to n:
  - if i % 15 === 0 => output 'FizzBuzz'
  - else if i % 3 === 0 => output 'Fizz'
  - else if i % 5 === 0 => output 'Buzz'
  - else => output String(i)

Configuration options and effects:
- divisors: [{divisor:3, token:'Fizz'}, {divisor:5, token:'Buzz'}] -- adding entries extends matching rules
- mode: 'array' | 'stream' -- determines whether returned value is materialised or written incrementally
- digitContains: boolean -- if true, also match when number contains the divisor digit

TROUBLESHOOTING

- Incorrect ordering (producing 'Fizz' instead of 'FizzBuzz'): ensure combined check (i%15===0) runs before single checks.
- Non-integer inputs: validate with Number.isInteger to avoid silent incorrect sequences.

